          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 104,
              "body": "````suggestion\nFinally, explicit Thread structure provides conversation context that is available to every Receiving Host. A Host can determine whether its local Participants have previously participated in a Thread and MAY use this information when making implementation-specific policy decisions, such as message classification, prioritisation or spam filtering.\n````",
              "createdAt": "2026-06-27T10:12:49Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-06-27T10:12:49Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 66,
              "body": "````suggestion\nFinally, to integrate sender verification and message integrity into the message exchange protocol. Rather than relying solely on complementary protocols or deployment-specific mechanisms, fmsg incorporates these properties into the architecture of message exchange itself. Hopefully simplifying deploying and operating hosts thereby enabling decentralisation of messaging providers.\n````",
              "createdAt": "2026-06-27T10:12:49Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-06-27T10:12:49Z"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
